Package org.openbel.framework.common.lang

Contains the immutable BEL language model.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
Abundance Denotes the abundance of an entity.
BiologicalProcess Denotes a process or population of events.
CatalyticActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events where a member acts as an enzymatic catalyst of biochecmial reactions.
CellSecretion Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which members of an abundance move from cells to regions outside of the cells.
CellSurfaceExpression Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which members of an abundance move to the surface of cells.
ChaperoneActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member binds to some substrate and acts as a chaperone for the substrate.
ComplexAbundance Denotes the abundance of a molecular complex.
CompositeAbundance Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which members are present.
Degradation Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member is degraded in some way such that it is no longer a member.
Function The base class of the immutable BEL function model.
Fusion Specifies the abundance of a protein translated from the fusion of a gene.
GeneAbundance Denotes the abundance of a gene.
GTPBoundActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member of a G-protein abundance is GTP-bound.
KinaseActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member acts as a kinase, performing enzymatic phosphorylation of a substrate.
MicroRNAAbundance Denotes the abundance of a processed, functional microRNA.
MolecularActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member acts as a causal agent at the molecular scale.
Pathology Denotes a disease or pathology process.
PeptidaseActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member acts to cleave a protein.
PhosphataseActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member acts as a phosphatase.
Products Denotes the products of a reaction.
ProteinAbundance Denotes the abundance of a protein.
ProteinModification Denotes a covalently modified protein abundance.
Reactants Denotes the reactants of a reaction.
Reaction Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in a reaction.
RibosylationActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member acts to perform post-translational modification of proteins.
RNAAbundance Denotes the abundance of a gene.
Signature Represents a BEL function signature.
Substitution Indicates the abundance of proteins with amino acid substitution sequence.
TermList Denotes a list of terms.
TranscriptionalActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member directly acts to control transcription of genes.
Translocation Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which members move between locations.
TransportActivity Denotes the frequency or abundance of events in which a member directs acts to enable the directed movement of substances into, out of, within, or between cells.
Truncation Indicates an abundance of proteins with truncation sequence variants.
 

Package org.openbel.framework.common.lang Description

Contains the immutable BEL language model.
